<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Mismatch on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/mismatch/</link><description>Recent content in Mismatch on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/mismatch/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Go Reflect Set Type Mismatch Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/reflect-set/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/reflect-set/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="reflectset-value-type-not-assignable--fix"&gt;Reflect.Set: Value Type Not Assignable — Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &amp;ldquo;reflect.Set: value of type X is not assignable to type Y&amp;rdquo; error occurs when you try to set a reflect value to a value of a different type.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;reflect.Value.Set()&lt;/code&gt; requires the new value to be assignable to the target type. If the types don&amp;rsquo;t match — even if they&amp;rsquo;re similar (like &lt;code&gt;int&lt;/code&gt; vs &lt;code&gt;int64&lt;/code&gt;) — the call panics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] React SSR Hydration Error — Server/Client Mismatch Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/react-ssr-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/react-ssr-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="react-ssr-hydration-error--serverclient-mismatch"&gt;React SSR Hydration Error — Server/Client Mismatch&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;Hydration failed because the initial UI does not match what was rendered on the server&lt;/code&gt; occurs when the server-rendered HTML does not match what React expects during client-side hydration. React detects the mismatch and falls back to client-only rendering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Server-Side Rendering (SSR), React renders components to HTML on the server, sends it to the client, then &amp;ldquo;hydrates&amp;rdquo; it by attaching event listeners and making it interactive. If the server and client produce different HTML, hydration fails.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Mismatched Types — Type Mismatch Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-mismatch-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-mismatch-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="mismatched-types--type-mismatch-error"&gt;Mismatched Types — Type Mismatch Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A compiler error with the message &amp;ldquo;mismatched types&amp;rdquo; occurs when you use a value of one type where a different type is expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust is statically typed — every expression has a known type at compile time. The compiler rejects code where the actual type doesn&amp;rsquo;t match the expected type. Unlike dynamic languages, Rust won&amp;rsquo;t silently convert between most types.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;String vs &amp;amp;str&lt;/strong&gt; — passing &lt;code&gt;String&lt;/code&gt; where &lt;code&gt;&amp;amp;str&lt;/code&gt; is expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Numeric mixing&lt;/strong&gt; — adding &lt;code&gt;i32&lt;/code&gt; + &lt;code&gt;f64&lt;/code&gt; without casting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wrong return type&lt;/strong&gt; — function returns wrong type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option vs value&lt;/strong&gt; — passing &lt;code&gt;Option&amp;lt;i32&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; where &lt;code&gt;i32&lt;/code&gt; is expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Result not unwrapped&lt;/strong&gt; — passing &lt;code&gt;Result&amp;lt;T, E&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; where &lt;code&gt;T&lt;/code&gt; is expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: String vs &amp;amp;str
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;(name: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hi &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, name); }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; String::from(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet(name); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: expected &amp;amp;str, found String
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Numeric type mismatch
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; x: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; y: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;f64&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.14&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; sum &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; y; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: cannot add f64 to i32
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Wrong return type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;get_number&lt;/span&gt;() -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;42&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: expected i32, found &amp;amp;str
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Bool where int expected
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; flag &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; count: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; flag; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: expected i32, found bool
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-borrow-or-convert-types"&gt;Fix 1: Borrow or convert types&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;(name: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hi &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, name); }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; String::from(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Option A: borrow
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;name);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Option B: convert
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet(name.as_str());
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-explicit-numeric-casting"&gt;Fix 2: Explicit numeric casting&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; x: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; y: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;f64&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3.14&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; sum &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;as&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;f64&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; y;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, sum); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// 8.14
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-return-the-correct-type"&gt;Fix 3: Return the correct type&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;get_number&lt;/span&gt;() -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Return a number, not a string
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-into-for-compatible-types"&gt;Fix 4: Use .into() for compatible types&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;(name: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;) { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hi &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, name); }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; String::from(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// String implements Into&amp;lt;&amp;amp;str&amp;gt; via deref
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;greet(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;name);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; x: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; y: &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;bool&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; y;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, result);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Mismatched Types / Expected X Found Y — Compiler Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-error8/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-error8/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="mismatched-types--expected-x-found-y"&gt;Mismatched Types / Expected X Found Y&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;mismatched types: expected X, found Y&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you provide a value of one type where the compiler expects a different type. Rust is statically typed and does not perform implicit type conversions (except for a few safe coercions).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s strong type system requires explicit type compatibility. The compiler infers types from context, but when two incompatible types are used in the same position, it produces a clear error message showing what was expected and what was found.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Type Mismatch — Mismatched Types Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-mismatch/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/type-mismatch/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="type-mismatch--mismatched-types-error"&gt;Type Mismatch — Mismatched Types Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A compiler error with the message &amp;ldquo;mismatched types&amp;rdquo; occurs when you try to use a value of one type where a different type is expected. Rust&amp;rsquo;s strong, static type system prevents this at compile time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust is strongly typed and performs type checking at compile time. The &amp;ldquo;mismatched types&amp;rdquo; error appears when:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A function receives the wrong argument type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A variable is assigned a value of the wrong type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A return value doesn&amp;rsquo;t match the declared return type.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pattern matching arms return different types.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Numeric types are mixed without explicit conversion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unlike dynamically typed languages, Rust won&amp;rsquo;t implicitly convert between most types. You must be explicit about type conversions.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SQLite Column Type Mismatch</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/sqlite/type-mismatch3/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/sqlite/type-mismatch3/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sqlite-column-type-mismatch"&gt;SQLite Column Type Mismatch&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A type mismatch error occurs when SQLite cannot convert a value to the expected column type. While SQLite is dynamically typed, type affinity rules can still cause unexpected behavior.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inserting a string into a column with INTEGER affinity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comparing values of incompatible types in WHERE clauses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using STRICT tables that enforce type checking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implicit type conversion produces unexpected results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-column-affinity"&gt;Check Column Affinity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;PRAGMA table_info(users);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-strict-tables-for-type-safety"&gt;Use STRICT Tables for Type Safety&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;CREATE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;TABLE&lt;/span&gt; users (
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; id INTEGER &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;PRIMARY&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;KEY&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; name TEXT &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;NOT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;NULL&lt;/span&gt;,
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; age INTEGER &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;NOT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;NULL&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;STRICT&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="cast-values-explicitly"&gt;Cast Values Explicitly&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INSERT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INTO&lt;/span&gt; users (id, name, age)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VALUES&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Alice&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;CAST&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;25&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; INTEGER));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-try_cast-for-safe-conversion"&gt;Use TRY_CAST for Safe Conversion&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- SQLite 3.44+
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INSERT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INTO&lt;/span&gt; users (id, name, age)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VALUES&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Alice&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, TRY_CAST(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;not-a-number&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;AS&lt;/span&gt; INTEGER));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- age will be NULL if conversion fails
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-comparison-queries"&gt;Fix Comparison Queries&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- WRONG: comparing integer column to string
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; age &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;25&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; age &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;25&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- STRICT table rejects wrong type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INSERT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;INTO&lt;/span&gt; users (id, name, age) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;VALUES&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Alice&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;twenty-five&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Error: cannot store TEXT value in INTEGER column age
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Type mismatch in comparison
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; id &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;abc&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Returns empty set (implicit conversion, no error but wrong results)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/sqlite/constraint-error/"&gt;Unique Constraint&lt;/a&gt; — duplicate value error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/sqlite/no-such-table/"&gt;No Such Table&lt;/a&gt; — table does not exist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Type mismatch</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/haskell/type-mismatch2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/haskell/type-mismatch2/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;Type mismatch&lt;/code&gt; error occurs during compilation when the type of an expression doesn&amp;rsquo;t match what&amp;rsquo;s expected. Haskell has a strong static type system, so these errors are caught at compile time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passing wrong type to function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect type annotation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mixing incompatible types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forgetting to convert between types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-haskell" data-lang="haskell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- WRONG: Type mismatch&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;add&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;add&lt;/span&gt; x y &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; x &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; y
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;add&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Type mismatch: expected Int, got String&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: Use matching types&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;add&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- 3&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-haskell" data-lang="haskell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- WRONG: Wrong type annotation&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;length&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;length&lt;/span&gt; xs &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; length xs &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- infinite recursion&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- CORRECT: Use correct type&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;length&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; [a] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Int&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;length&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;length&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;_&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;xs) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; length xs
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-haskell" data-lang="haskell"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Example 1: Wrong argument type&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;not&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hello&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Type mismatch: expected Bool, got String&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Example 2: Wrong return type&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;head&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt; [a] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; a
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;head&lt;/span&gt; (x&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;xs) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; xs &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Type mismatch: expected a, got [a]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Example 3: Mixing types&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;True&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Type mismatch: Can&amp;#39;t match Bool with Int&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/haskell/variable-not-in-scope"&gt;Variable not in scope&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/haskell/ghc-error"&gt;GHC compilation error&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>